{"type":"message","id":"f3bb38b7","parentId":"41cc6acf","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:06:36.958Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nzx7cy0g6rgx_2","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4113\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=0\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=0\r\n[master 82835aa] pulse: 2026-03-24 120614\n 3 files changed, 174 insertions(+), 79 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 120614.md\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 120614 - The CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) while only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). This suggests frequency-based compression discards signal while keeping noise. A controlled experiment comparing CFI-weighted vs frequency-only compression is the logical next step.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"quick-daisy","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4113\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=0\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=0\r\n[master 82835aa] pulse: 2026-03-24 120614\n 3 files changed, 174 insertions(+), 79 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 120614.md\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 120614 - The CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) while only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). This suggests frequency-based compression discards signal while keeping noise. A controlled experiment comparing CFI-weighted vs frequency-only compression is the logical next step.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774368396956}}
