{"type":"message","id":"0736e8c6","parentId":"bbef302c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:06:39.925Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_i07yltje6nfe_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 120507\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. CFI Analysis was just completed (2026-03-24) - finding that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are noise (CFI=0)\r\n3. Pending items include:\r\n   - CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n   - Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n   - Distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\nThe next logical step based on the pending items and the CFI findings would be to design and set up the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would involve:\r\n\r\n1. Creating a comparison between frequency-only compression vs CFI-weighted compression\r\n2. Measuring prediction quality across pulses\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action that advances this goal. I should create a research document that outlines the CFI-weighted compression experiment design, which would then serve as the blueprint for implementation.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the notes - the CFI results were just found. The next step from the findings is to run the CFI-weighted compression experiment. Let me create a concrete experiment design document that specifies:\r\n1. How to weight by CFI\r\n2. How to compare vs frequency baseline\r\n3. Success metrics\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete file creation that advances the goals.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0), while only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). The immediate next step is to design and implement a CFI-weighted compression experiment to test whether CFI-weighting improves next-pulse prediction quality over frequency-only baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the CFI-weighted compression experiment design document that specifies methodology, success metrics, and implementation approach for comparing CFI-weighted vs frequency-only compression.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** Ready for implementation\r\n**Priority:** HIGH - tests core hypothesis that CFI > frequency for trajectory prediction\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n\r\nCFI-weighted compression should outperform frequency-only compression for predicting the next pulse's research trajectory because:\r\n- CFI filters out metaprogramming artifacts (noise) that inflate frequency counts\r\n- CFI preserves true causal anchors (research decisions, key insights)\r\n- Frequency compresses equally toward noise and signal\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Setup\r\n1. Take current pulse history as corpus\r\n2. Compute invariants across all pulses using existing frequency analysis\r\n3. Apply CFI scoring to each invariant\r\n4. Compare two compression strategies on held-out pulse\r\n\r\n### Compression Strategies\r\n\r\n**Strategy A: Frequency-Only (Baseline)**\r\n```\r\nweight(invariant) = frequency(invariant) / total_tokens\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Strategy B: CFI-Weighted (Test)**\r\n```\r\nweight(invariant) = CFI(invariant) * frequency(invariant) / total_tokens\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Prediction Task\r\nGiven compressed representation of pulses 1..N, predict presence/absence of each invariant in pulse N+1.\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n1. **Precision@K**: Of top-K predicted invariants, what fraction appear in pulse N+1?\r\n2. **Recall@K**: Of actual invariants in pulse N+1, what fraction in top-K predictions?\r\n3. **F1@K**: Harmonic mean of precision and recall\r\n4. **Compression Ratio**: tokens(compressed) / tokens(original)\r\n\r\n### Implementation Steps\r\n1. Extract invariants from pulse_*.md files using existing frequency analysis\r\n2. Compute CFI for each invariant (using code from `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`)\r\n3. Build two separate compressed representations\r\n4. Run prediction on held-out pulse\r\n5. Compare metrics\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\n\r\n| Metric | Frequency-Only | CFI-Weighted |\r\n|--------|---------------|--------------|\r\n| Precision@10 | ~0.3 | >0.5 |\r\n| Recall@10 | ~0.4 | >0.5 |\r\n| F1@10 | ~0.35 | >0.5 |\r\n| Compression Ratio | ~0.6 | ~0.4 |\r\n\r\nIf CFI-weighted performs worse, it would indicate:\r\n- CFI is over-filtering (removing useful low-CFI signals)\r\n- Frequency captures useful patterns CFI misses\r\n- Need hybrid approach\r\n\r\n## Files Needed\r\n- `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` - for CFI scoring algorithm\r\n- `research/FREQUENCY_ANALYSIS.md` - for invariant extraction\r\n- Pulse history: `pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\n## Success Criterion\r\n\r\nCFI-weighted F1@10 >= 1.3x Frequency-only F1@10\r\n\r\nThis validates that CFI filtering removes noise without losing predictive signal.\r\n`\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n`\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:05:36\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774368399923}}
{"type":"message","id":"3a16a2f8","parentId":"0736e8c6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:06:46.772Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me read the newest log file to get the actual OBSERVATION from the latest pulse cycle.","thinkingSignature":"a927d472430a430556044d64f09401a188540000650c18f0f57a3a1bb6835b2d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_se9nyb1lbz5k_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 120614.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1845,"output":74,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14056,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774368399925}}
{"type":"message","id":"14d1de70","parentId":"3a16a2f8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:06:46.778Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_se9nyb1lbz5k_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 120614\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and think about what concrete action I can take to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent status:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Just completed CFI Analysis with findings about frequency-invariants\r\n\r\nPending actions:\r\n1. CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n2. Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n3. Distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Design actual compression network\r\n\r\nLooking at the CFI results:\r\n- 44.8% have CFI=0 (pure noise/metaprogramming artifacts)\r\n- Only 5.7% have CFI>=0.7 (true causal anchors)\r\n- Mean CFI is 0.181\r\n\r\nThe most actionable next step seems to be the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would involve:\r\n1. Taking the existing frequency-based compression data\r\n2. Creating a CFI-weighted version\r\n3. Comparing next-pulse prediction quality\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist that could help me set up this experiment. I need to see the frequency analysis data and understand how to apply CFI weighting.\r\n\r\nActually, let me first check what data exists. The CFI_RESULTS.md mentions analyzing frequency-invariants but I need to see what the actual data structure looks like to design the experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: design the CFI-weighted compression experiment specification. This would be a new file that outlines:\r\n1. The hypothesis\r\n2. The methodology\r\n3. The success metrics\r\n4. The implementation steps\r\n\r\nThis is specific, advances the pending goal, and results in a file edit (new file creation).\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) while only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). This suggests frequency-based compression discards signal while keeping noise. A controlled experiment comparing CFI-weighted vs frequency-only compression is the logical next step.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate an experiment specification for CFI-weighted compression, defining methodology, metrics, and implementation approach to validate whether filtering by CFI threshold improves next-pulse prediction quality compared to frequency baseline.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-only compression in next-pulse prediction quality because it filters out metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) while preserving true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7).\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Baseline: Frequency-Only Compression\r\n- Keep top N% by frequency\r\n- Metric: next-pulse coherence score\r\n\r\n### Treatment: CFI-Weighted Compression\r\n- Formula: weight = CFI^α × freq^β\r\n- Filter: CFI > threshold (0.3)\r\n- Metric: next-pulse coherence score\r\n\r\n### Coherence Metrics\r\n1. **Concept overlap**: % of predicted concepts present in actual pulse\r\n2. **Trajectory continuity**: Did research direction continue or pivot?\r\n3. **Goal state accuracy**: Was the intended goal advanced?\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n### Data Needed\r\n- Full frequency-invariant set from CFI analysis\r\n- CFI scores for each invariant\r\n- Historical pulse sequence for ground truth\r\n\r\n### Method\r\n```\r\nFor each pulse p in test set:\r\n  1. Extract frequency invariants from context\r\n  2. Apply baseline: top 50% by freq\r\n  3. Apply treatment: top 50% by (CFI × freq), CFI > 0.3\r\n  4. Predict next concepts from each compression\r\n  5. Compare predictions vs actual pulse p+1\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- Treatment > Baseline on ≥2 of 3 metrics\r\n- Statistical significance (p < 0.05) across 20+ test pulses\r\n\r\n## Files to Create\r\n- `experiment/cfi_compression_test_set.txt` - pulses to test\r\n- `experiment/baseline_predictions.json` - frequency-only predictions\r\n- `experiment/treatment_predictions.json` - CFI-weighted predictions\r\n- `experiment/results.md` - comparison report\r\n`\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n`\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:06:36\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774368406776}}
